## Run plan (waves & branches)

This is a **greenfield build-from-spec** run: the B-/F- tickets above ARE the inbox, so there is **no
discovery wave** — fixers drain the queue starting at Wave 1. (In discovery/audit mode the numbering
shifts: Wave 1 = discovery, Wave 2 = fix, Wave 3 = re-verify — see PROTOCOL §1 / PLAYBOOK §4.)

Sequential waves; parallel within a wave. Every sub-agent runs in an **isolated worktree**, commits
its **own branch**, and **never pushes**. Branch names embed a session-short id so concurrent
sessions can't collide: `{{TRACK}}/{{PHASE}}-{{TICKET_ID}}-s{{SESSION_SHORT}}`.

| Wave | Runs | Parallelism | Tickets | Notes |
|------|------|-------------|---------|-------|
| **0 — Baseline + plan** | orchestrator captures the baseline + writes this run-plan | orchestrator alone | — | Baseline keyed by HEAD SHA + `BASELINE-NOTES`; no spawns yet. |
| **1a — Foundation (SOLO)** | data model + contracts + RBAC/audit/state-machine primitives | 1 agent | the B-ticket that creates `{{MODULE_NAME}}.contract.ts`, the schema file, and the migration | Tag a checkpoint **before** the migration. Everything below leans on this — it lands alone so there's no race on the seams. |
| **1b — Build (PARALLEL)** | API + web feature tickets | up to {{MAX_PARALLEL}} agents | remaining `B-{{AREA}}-*` and `F-{{AREA}}-*` | Each owns its module globs; appends to seams; mocked API for web e2e. No contracts version bump. |
| **2 — Re-verify** | re-run gates per branch | parallel | every branch from 1a/1b | Re-verifiers re-run the universal gate against each branch vs the baseline. They do NOT integrate. |

> **Integration is NOT a wave of this build run.** Once Wave 2 is green, run `/kit-integrate` as a
> **separate** gated pass — a pre-merge Opus `pr-reviewer` gate, merge in documented order, then the
> integrator (and only the integrator) bumps the contracts version + regenerates `openapi.yaml`/
> `api-types` ONCE and re-emits atomic conventional commits. It does NOT push or open a PR. See
> PLAYBOOK §5. Folding integration into the build run is the single most-repeated anti-pattern in the
> kit (LESSONS L4/L10, PROTOCOL §10).

### Gate commands (the universal gate)

```bash
{{TYPECHECK_CMD}}        # clean
{{LINT_CMD}}             # clean
{{UNIT_TEST_CMD}}        # green
{{CONTRACTS_BUILD_CMD}}  # contracts build clean
{{E2E_CMD}}              # browser/e2e green (mocked early; real composed stack late)
```

Capture a **baseline** keyed by HEAD SHA + a `BASELINE-NOTES` listing pre-existing failures, so a
regression is distinguishable from an inherited failure. Every commit must be independently green.

### Dependencies

- `1b` cannot start until `1a` is merged (the contract + schema + primitives must exist).
- Frontend tickets that need a live endpoint either mock it (early) or wait for the matching backend
  ticket (late). Record the dependency in each ticket's `blocked_by`.
